This paper deals with the evaluation of recursive neural network models and their vector representations for words in capturing linguistic meaning necessary for interpretation or reasoning. This makes it likely to belong to the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), and computer vision (cs.CV) as these categories are closely related to the topic of the paper.
